        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 30 at 9:21PM EDT by NWS Cleveland OH</headline>
        <description>At 921 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Bellevue, or 14 miles west of Norwalk, moving southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Norwalk, Bellevue, Willard, Monroeville, North Fairfield, and Flat
Rock.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
